    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Paramedic - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_paramedic">Paramedic</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_professional">CARE PROFESSIONAL</xref>
 who is registered with the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_health_and_care_professions_council">Health and Care Professions Council</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_paramedic">Paramedic</xref>
 provides specialist care and treatment to 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 who are either acutely ill or injured. They can administer a range of drugs and carry out certain surgical techniques.        </p>
  </div>
